Celebration Park Naples
is a vibrant waterfront destination offering a unique blend of gourmet food trucks, a full liquor bar, and live music. Located in the Bayshore Arts District, it provides a relaxed, outdoor atmosphere perfect for enjoying delicious food, refreshing drinks, and scenic views. Whether you’re here for a casual meal, dancing to live performances, or hosting a special event, Celebration Park is your go-to spot for a fun and memorable experience in Naples, Florida.

about
our story
swfl’s original food truck park; located in the heart of the bayshore arts district
it all started in 2018…
We offer a lively waterfront destination in the Bayshore District, offering a unique industrial vibe with a full liquor bar and rows of food trucks. Overlooking a waterway with access to the Gulf of Mexico,
the park was inspired by global food truck scenes and created by owner Rebecca Maddox. She also owns Rebecca’s, and The MADDOX. Visitors can arrive by land or boat, bringing their dogs along to enjoy diverse food, specialty cocktails, cold beer, and daily live music from local artists.

Thank you to everyone who came out for our pop up Yoga Event by Yoga Lab
Posted at 11:57h
in
Bayshore Arts District
,

,

,
Private Events

We’re still buzzing from all the good vibes this past weekend at
Celebration Park
! Our pop-up yoga session with
Yoga Lab
was an absolute hit, and we couldn’t have asked for a more beautiful day in the
Bayshore Arts District
.
The energy was incredible as locals and visitors alike rolled out their mats under the sun, surrounded by the vibrant atmosphere of our food truck park. From start to finish, it was the kind of event that reminds us why we love being a hub for the community — where wellness, fun, and flavor meet.
A huge shoutout to
Steven Nguyen
and
Jillian Hite
for leading such an inspiring and energizing session. You both absolutely crushed it, and we’re so grateful for the work you put into making this event a success. Thank you for sharing your passion with our space and bringing people together through movement and mindfulness.
We also want to thank everyone who came out to support, stretch, and flow with us. Your positive energy and enthusiasm made the morning unforgettable. It was amazing to see so many smiling faces soaking up the sunshine and taking time for wellness in such a unique setting.
We’re already thinking about doing this again — maybe even turning it into a regular series. What do you think? Would you join us for more
yoga at the park
? Let us know in the comments or shoot us a message — we’d love to hear from you.
From all of us at Celebration Park, thank you again for being part of such a memorable day. Stay tuned for more community events coming soon — and until then, keep those good vibes flowing!
